amuse /əˈmjuːz/

(amusing,amused,amuses) 

1. V-T If something amuses you, it makes you want to laugh or smile. 使发笑 

例： The thought seemed to amuse him. 这个想法好像让他觉得好笑。 

2. V-T If you amuse yourself , you do something in order to pass the time and not become bored. 使消遣 

例： I need distractions. I need to amuse myself so I won't keep thinking about things. 我需要娱乐。我需要自我消遣，这样我才不会一直想事情。 

3.  →  see also amused , amusing

